commit.message: Update with information about current project status.

Improve testing for CompressionInfo.db files.

 - When testing for a CompressionInfo.db file adjacent to the Data.db
   sstable, if the file cannot be found test the path to see if it
   looks like it contains a date time.  When it does contain a date
   time check the adjacent minutes around the Data.db file to see if
   they contain the CompressionInfo.db file.

   This is condition exists because sometimes Priam uploads the 
   Data.db and CompressionInfo.db files in separate minutes.

Issue #56: Fixes an OOM error processing large compressed column families. (#57)

- Switch to using try with resources to close streams.
 - additionally don't store data in memory that we are not using (when only calculating the end of the stream).
Ensure checksum is fully read until EOF. (#55)
Fixed combining splits for compressed column families.

Use -combineSplits to combine input splits.

 - This feature already existed in older versions of Aegisthus.  This is
   especially useful for reducing the number of mappers when processing
   incremental changes.

   Most code for AegisthusCombinedInputFormat, CombineSSTableReader,
and AegCombinedSplit were resurrected from the code that existed in
4cc53ef653dc3c0a367c349901ae8cc31fce02de.
Upgrade Gradle and Nebula plugins.

Added an option to trace data from the source.

 - When the hadoop config “aegisthus.trace_source” is true,
   Aegisthus will keep track of which source sstable all data was
   loaded from.  NOTE: Currently this data can only be output in
   the JSON output format.  This is not the normal Aegisthus output
   and is only useful for debugging.

Updated README.

Added a section to document how to test Aegisthus and another section with ideas for future enhancements.

Work around to process C* 2.1 and 2.2 data

 - This is a temporary patch.  The long term solution
   is to upgrade Aegisthus to use the Cassandra
   2.2 libraries.
Allow tests to ignore timestamps when comparing output.

Testing updates.

 - Migrated tests from Test-NG to jUnit
 - Moved aegisthus-test into aegisthus-hadoop.
adding OSSMETADATA for NetflixOSS tracking

Fix getDataFiles removing FS schema and bucket.

 - pathsString only worked on the path and dropped the schema and
   bucket so this is reworked so that you can use s3 for your input
   directory instead of hdfs if you want to (mainly useful for testing).

Calculate split sizes in parallel.

 - Previously splits were calculated sequentially.  Doing this in 
   parallel provides a substantial performance improvement for jobs
   that are reading many data files.
Moving log statement to debug level.

Index was off by one when there is deleted data.

 - Additionally broke out and added comments to make it easier to
   follow while I was tracking down the issue.

Kill the hadoop job if Aegisthus is interrupted.

 - This is enabled by default but can be disabled with
   -Daegisthus.shutdown_hook=false

Merge pull request #45 from coursera/dan-opt-key-2

Use raw comparator

Merge pull request #43 from rspieldenner/netflixoss

Netflixoss
use raw comparator
Remove if blocks which switch between internal and external builds
Remove unneeded version field
Switch to updated netflixoss build
Fix for shuffling when there are deletes.
Fix for a shuffle NPE.
Fix for an error when processing deleted items.

Merge pull request #39 from danielbwatson/c2_merge

C2 Support
Bump version to 0.3.1.

Allow automatically skipping corrupted files.

 - Configured with the property: aegisthus.max_corrupt_files_to_skip
 - Defaults to 0.
 - Removed aegisthus.skip_rows_with_errors
   Because of the file format it is frequently difficult to tell if a file or a whole row is corrupted, therefore we count any file with errors as corrupted.
